        <h1>üë£ Digital Footprints</h1>

        <p><strong>What is a digital footprint?</strong><br>
        Your digital footprint is the trail of data you leave behind when you use the internet. Every post, photo, comment, like, search, and click creates a record that can last forever ‚Äì even if you delete it!</p>

        <h2>What Creates Your Digital Footprint?</h2>
        <div class="footprint-example">
          <div class="footprint-item">
            <div class="icon">üì∏</div>
            <strong>Photos & Videos</strong>
            <p>Everything you upload</p>
          </div>
          <div class="footprint-item">
            <div class="icon">üí¨</div>
            <strong>Comments</strong>
            <p>What you say online</p>
          </div>
          <div class="footprint-item">
            <div class="icon">üë§</div>
            <strong>Accounts</strong>
            <p>Profiles you create</p>
          </div>
          <div class="footprint-item">
            <div class="icon">‚ù§Ô∏è</div>
            <strong>Likes & Shares</strong>
            <p>What you interact with</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Why Your Digital Footprint Matters</h2>
        <div class="info-box">
          <h3>üéì Your Future Self Will Thank You</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>College applications:</strong> Admissions officers look at social media</li>
            <li><strong>Job opportunities:</strong> 70% of employers check candidates online</li>
            <li><strong>Scholarships:</strong> Review committees research applicants</li>
            <li><strong>Friendships:</strong> People form opinions based on what you post</li>
            <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Personal info can be used against you</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>How to Keep Your Footprint Positive</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Think before you post</strong> ‚Äì Once it's online, it's there forever</li>
          <li><strong>Be kind in comments</strong> ‚Äì Would you say it to someone's face?</li>
          <li><strong>Don't overshare personal info</strong> ‚Äì Keep your address, phone number, and school private</li>
          <li><strong>Use privacy settings</strong> ‚Äì Make accounts private when possible</li>
          <li><strong>Google yourself</strong> ‚Äì See what others can find about you</li>
          <li><strong>Report bullying or harassment</strong> ‚Äì Don't let negativity define your footprint</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The Screenshot Reality</h2>
        <p>Even if you delete a post, someone might have already:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>üì± Taken a screenshot</li>
          <li>üíæ Downloaded it</li>
          <li>‚ÜóÔ∏è Shared it with others</li>
          <li>ü§ñ Had it archived by search engines</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-weight: 600; color: #f44336; margin-top: 12px;">The internet never forgets!</p>

        <div class="golden-rule">
          ‚≠ê Golden Rule ‚≠ê<br>
          If you wouldn't say it in a school assembly,<br>
          don't post it online!
        </div>

        <div class="challenge-box">
          <h3>üêµ Monkey Challenge</h3>
          <p>Think about the last thing you posted, liked, or commented on social media.</p>
          <p><strong>Now imagine it being shown on a giant screen in your school cafeteria.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; margin-top: 16px;">If that thought makes you cringe or feel embarrassed, that's your brain telling you something important about your digital choices!</p>
          
          <h4 style="margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #d97706;">Quick Quiz:</h4>
          <p style="font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; color: #333;">Which action leaves the SMALLEST digital footprint?</p>
          
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            A) Posting a video of yourself dancing on TikTok
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">
            B) Texting your friend privately about weekend plans
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            C) Commenting "This is so dumb!" on a celebrity's Instagram post
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            D) Posting a photo of your house with the address visible
          </div>

          <div id="quiz-feedback" class="quiz-feedback"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="complete-checkbox">
          <input type="checkbox" id="lesson-complete" onchange="markComplete()">
          <label for="lesson-complete">‚úÖ I've completed this lesson!</label>
        </div>

        <a href="done.html" class="btn">Finish All Lessons! üéâ</a>
